          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "More than 50 Congressional Democrats sent a letter to House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Majority Leader Steny Hoyer calling for them to end fossil fuel subsidies as part of the bipartisan infrastructure bill. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "“We are writing to request that you include the repeal of fossil fuel subsidies in the Build Back Better Act,” the letter said. “In his fiscal year 2022 budget, President Biden committed to the inclusion of $121 billion in revenue raised from repealing fossil fuel subsidies, which includes $86 billion from tax breaks for foreign oil and gas income… Congress must follow through in implementing the President’s vision.”",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
